        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 3 at 5:12PM CDT by NWS Dodge City KS</headline>
        <description>At 512 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ford, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Ford around 515 PM CDT.
Bucklin around 525 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
